6.21	Needle_gun	Needle gun	A needle gun is a firearm that has a needle-like firing pin, which can pass through the paper cartridge case to strike a percussion cap at the bullet base. A needle gun with a barrel that has a helical groove or pattern of grooves ("rifling") cut into the barrel walls is also called needle rifle.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/53/Dreyse_needle_gun_model_1865.jpg/330px-Dreyse_needle_gun_model_1865.jpg
